50|$|William Clifford 'Cliff' Richards (28 March 1901 - 13 February 1964) was a Welsh {{international}} rugby union wing {{who played}} club rugby for Pontypool and Swansea and represented Wales at international level. Richards was a coal miner by trade, and <b>worked</b> <b>in</b> the <b>pits</b> all his adult life. In 1964, {{while working at}} the Navigation Colliery in Crumlin, {{he was killed in}} an underground accident.|$|R
