50|$|Coal was mined in New Manchester {{where the}} coal seams of the Manchester Coalfield outcrop {{and are not}} far below the surface.The {{community}} was in existence by 1803 in houses provided by the Duke of Bridgewater who owned the mining rights. The men who came to <b>work</b> <b>in</b> the <b>pits</b> named the streets after places in their hometown, Manchester, Shude Hill, Gatley Row and City Road, the only road into the village.|$|R
