50|$|The cross roads {{where all}} these roads meet is today known as Ryan's Cross. This {{is named after}} a mining family of Ryans who <b>worked</b> <b>in</b> the <b>pits</b> for {{hundreds}} of years. In past times it was common for timber boards to be laid on the road at the crossroads so that the people from far afield could in the long summer evenings meet to enjoy themselves by dancing on the boards.|$|R
25|$|The {{solid red}} flag is {{displayed}} when conditions are {{too dangerous to}} continue the session. Depending on the series and the circumstances, the cars are typically directed to proceed immediately to pit road, or to stop at a specific spot on the track. In some severe cases the cars might be required to stop immediately where they are. During red flag conditions, repair <b>work</b> <b>in</b> the <b>pits</b> or garage area is typically prohibited, except in non-points paying races.|$|R
